         <abstract id="aspace_6aca0ce8c421534aa8e91a23f1dc1997">This collection consists of administrative records of Bulldogs Across America, an alumni-sponsored summer internship progrma for Yale students. The records include newpaper and magazine articles about the program, agreements with local programs and Yale University, correspondence, financial information, and electronic records.  </abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <corpname source="local">
               <part>Yale University. Bulldogs Across America</part>
            </corpname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
      <bioghist id="aspace_26a94ce65dc960bff6e28f3854609011">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Bulldogs Across America, founded in 1999, is a program for Yale undergraduate students that provides alumni-sponsored summer internships in several different cities around the United States. The program offers students work experience in both the for-profit and non-profit sectors, networking and educational opportunities, and mentorship from Yale alumni.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_ca4c22dfbd203ed54df8fa62a1648003">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection consists of administrative records of Bulldogs Across America including newpaper and magazine articles about the program, agreements with local programs and Yale University, correspondence, financial information, and electronic records.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <prefercite id="aspace_9aba39451f134f97a0765e05a36f651f">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Bulldogs Across America, Yale College, Records (RU 1125). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_84844c4adf4b02dd13aa737d84ddf312">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged as received.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <userestrict id="aspace_b273df34a2781ba99395b3499ccfefe5">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright to any materials created by John Rowan Claypool V are held by him until February 7, 2050, or his death, whichever occurs first, at which time all rights are transferred to Yale University.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_d67c30d3cefc311ccdcc4a59d36fcb6a">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>Access prohibited for 35 years from creation of the records.</p>
         <p>Original born digital files, as well as preservation masters, may not be accessed due to their fragility. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist request that they be made. Born digital files cannot be accessed remotely. System requirements include a Manuscripts and Archives computer and file viewing software.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <odd id="aspace_cb8383d435e97e0e8b6984426a7da989">
         <head>General</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 9-E (YRG 9-E), Records documenting Yale College offices, programs, and projects.</p>  
      </odd>
